abstract = {The founding, organization, and growth of large urban agglomerations throughout history have generated significant challenges for transportation and mobility systems. Public transportation is considered an essential piece in sustainable urban developments, since it allows the achievement of more efficient movements and flows within a city, thus significantly decreasing the use of cars and reducing environmental pollution. However, making the right decisions to establish efficient urban transportation routes is becoming more complex, thus it is necessary to have innovative and useful methods that consider urban growth among other factors to solve transport problems. Through the suitable design of a transportation system and the location of its stops, it is possible to reduce travel times and timeouts and increase user satisfaction. There are several restrictions to consider, such as the number of passengers that can travel in a bus, passenger demand, the size of the bus fleet, and more. These restrictions must be taken into consideration when determining optimal routes, number of stops, waiting times, and so on. In this chapter, we use Spider Monkey Optimization (SMO) to plan a public transportation route in an urban municipality in Mexico.}
